Privacy Policy
1. Introducti
on
We are committed to protecting your privacy and handling your data in an open and transparent manner. This policy explains how we collec
t, use, and share your personal data when you use our educational services.
​
2. Information We Collect
2.1 Personal Information
When you create an account or profile with aiLaMo, we collect personal data, such as your name, email address, and payment information.
2.2 Usage Information
We collect data regarding your use of our services. This includes information such as progress on our courses, time spent on the app, your interactions with our services, and any problems or issues you encounter.
2.3 Cookies and Similar Technologies
aiLaMo uses cookies and other tracking technologies to identify you, remember your preferences, monitor user engagement, improve our services, and deliver a personalized experience.
​
3. Use of Information
3.1 Service Delivery
We primarily use your data to provide, personalize, and enhance our educational services. This includes tracking your progress, suggesting relevant courses, improving app performance, and sending necessary updates and administrative messages.
3.2 Data Analysis
We use collected data to understand user behavior and trends, enhance app functionality, and improve our educational content.
3.3 Legal Compliance
We may use your data to comply with applicable laws, regulations, legal processes, or enforceable governmental requests.
​
4. Data Sharing and Disclosure
4.1 No Third-Party Sharing
We do not share your personal data with third parties for their marketing purposes. We may share anonymized, aggregated data for industry analysis and demographic profiling.
4.2 Legal Obligations
We may disclose your data if we believe it's necessary to comply with a law, regulation, legal process, or governmental request.
​
5. Data Security
We're committed to safeguarding your data. We implement various security measures such as access controls and secure databases. However, no s
ecurity system is impenetrable, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.
​
6. Children's Privacy
aiLaMo is not intended for children u
nder 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we discover that a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, we promptly delete such information.
​
7. Changes to Our Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy occasionally. If we make significant changes, we'll notify you via the email linked to your account or display a notice on our site.
​
8. Your Rights
You have the right to access, update, or delete your personal data. You also have the right to withdraw your consent at any time where aiLaMo relied on your consent to proces
s your personal data.
​
9. Contact Us
For any questions, concerns, or comments about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at
info@ailamo.com
By using aiLaMo, you consent to our Privacy Policy, effective from
July 3, 2023.